      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Search</a> * <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">Score</a> * Millipawns</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Millipede.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Millipede.jpg/330px-Millipede.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Millipede.jpg/500px-Millipede.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/92/Millipede.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Millipede.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Millipede <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Millipawns</b>, (Milli-pawns)<br />\na score unit which corresponds approximately to <b>one thousandth</b> of a <a href=\"/Pawn_Advantage,_Win_Percentage,_and_Elo\" title=\"Pawn Advantage, Win Percentage, and Elo\">pawn unit</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fixed-point_arithmetic\">Fixed point</a> representation with millipawn fractions allows a smooth relation of all <a href=\"/Point_Value\" title=\"Point Value\">piece values</a> with a finer granularity than <a href=\"/Centipawns\" title=\"Centipawns\">centipawns</a> to distinguish positional scores. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Doch\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Doch</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Doch\">Doch</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Millipawns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Doch\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><a href=\"/Don_Dailey\" title=\"Don Dailey\">Don Dailey</a> on the evaluation grain in <a href=\"/Doch\" title=\"Doch\">Doch</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>:\n</p>\n<pre>The key thing to understand is that chess programs compare positions better than they evaluate them. Since most of the positions you compare are very similar (most of the pieces are sitting on the same squares) even a tiny difference can distinguish one similar position from another and even do it correctly. Even though neither position may have a very accurate evaluation, your evaluations function is more likely than not to pick the best one of the two given a choice as it will likely have more of something \"good\" in one of them, or less of something \"bad\". \n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Millipawns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Centipawns\" title=\"Centipawns\">Centipawns</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Pawn_Advantage,_Win_Percentage,_and_Elo\" title=\"Pawn Advantage, Win Percentage, and Elo\">Pawn Advantage, Win Percentage, and Elo</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Point_Value\" title=\"Point Value\">Point Value</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Millipawns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29694\">Centipawns and Millipawns</a> by Ricardo Gibert, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 08, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75501\">Centipawns vs Millipawns with NNUE</a> by Madeleine Birchfield, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 23, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/NNUE\" title=\"NNUE\">NNUE</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Millipawns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/milli-\">milli- - Wiktionary</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milli-\">Milli- from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fixed-point_arithmetic\">Fixed-point arithmetic from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Granularity\">Granularity from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resolution\">Resolution from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rounding\">Rounding from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Category:John_Coltrane\" title=\"Category:John Coltrane\">John Coltrane Quartet</a> - <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Love_Supreme\">Resolution</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> Video </li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a href=\"/Category:McCoy_Tyner\" title=\"Category:McCoy Tyner\">McCoy Tyner</a>, <a href=\"/Category:Elvin_Jones\" title=\"Category:Elvin Jones\">Elvin Jones</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Garrison\">Jimmy Garrison</a>, <a href=\"/Category:John_Coltrane\" title=\"Category:John Coltrane\">John Coltrane</a></dd>\n<dd> <div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/O6pSffe4k60?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></dd></dl>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Millipawns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Photograph of a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Millipede\">millipede</a> taken by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Marshman\">Eric Guinther</a> on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oahu\">O'ahu</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii\">Hawai'i</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Trigoniulus_corallinus\">Trigoniulus corallinus - Wikimedia Commons</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29694&amp;start=10\">Re: Centipawns and Millipawns</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Dailey\" title=\"Don Dailey\">Don Dailey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 08, 2009</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301032633\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.065 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.603 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 56/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 138/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 26/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:2076-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301032632 and revision id 21874\n -->\n"
